---
name: distributed-map
description: v1.22 — .map(named("double")).collect() round-trip across 3 nodes
backends: [jvm]
---

# Distributed map — named handler round-trip

Tests a `map` with a named handler dispatched across a 3-node in-process
cluster.  The handler doubles integers.  Result is collected and sorted
for deterministic output.

[Node, Cluster](std/mapreduce/cluster.ssc)

[NamedHandler, HandlerRegistry, named](std/mapreduce/handlers.ssc)

[StageOp, MapOp, Stage, WorkerProtocol, runDistributed, DistributedResult](std/mapreduce/distributed.ssc)

```scalascript
runActors {
  // Register the named handler on every worker (same codebase deployment)
  val doubleFn: Int => Int = (x: Int) => x * 2
  HandlerRegistry.register(NamedHandler("double", doubleFn))

  // Simulate 3 worker actors using WorkerProtocol
  val w1 = spawn { () => WorkerProtocol.handleMessages() }
  val w2 = spawn { () => WorkerProtocol.handleMessages() }
  val w3 = spawn { () => WorkerProtocol.handleMessages() }

  val nodes: List[Node] = List(
    Node("w1@localhost:9101"),
    Node("w2@localhost:9102"),
    Node("w3@localhost:9103")
  )
  val pids: List[Any] = List(w1, w2, w3)
  val cluster: Cluster = Cluster(nodes, pids)

  val data: List[Any] = List(1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9)
  val ops: List[StageOp] = List(MapOp("double"))
  val stage: Stage = Stage(ops)

  val result: DistributedResult[Any] = runDistributed(data, stage, cluster, 0, false)

  val sorted = result.results.asInstanceOf[List[Int]].sortBy(x => x)
  sorted.foreach(x => println(x))
  cluster.close()
}
```
